## 3. TWO-STAGE COMPUTATIONAL ARCHITECTURE

You must maintain a strict separation between discrete structural filtering and continuous parameter optimization to protect hardware resources.

```
[ LLM Stochastic Proposals ] 
             │ (Raw Strings of Expressions)
             ▼
┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ STAGE 1: COARSE SCREENING LOOP (CPU / SymPy)           │
│ 1. Parser Gatekeeper (Syntax check via AST Parsing)   │
│ 2. Dimensional Homogeneity Filter                      │
│ 3. SymPy Symbolic Limit Evaluation (ARC Score Check)   │
│ 4. Complexity Penalty (Occam's Razor)                  │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
             │ 
             ▼ (Top 5% Structurally Sound Candidates Only)
┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│ STAGE 2: FINE OPTIMIZATION LOOP (JAX CPU Mode)         │
│ 1. Dynamic Lambdify Translation (SymPy -> JAX Graph)   │
│ 2. Continuous Parameter Vector (θ) Optimization        │
│ 3. Symplectic Integration & Pareto Frontier Extraction  │
└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

